bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there,
My name is Madison, I am 29 years old. I am a responsible, caring, and fun caregiver! I have over 5 years of experience as a nanny and have been babysitting for 14 years. I have experience taking care of children of all ages- from infant to 13 years old.

As a caregiver, I am committed to providing a safe, nurturing environment to the children in my care. I am also able to help with household work and errands as needed.

I am a career professional, currently in between roles, so I am looking for part-time employment. I am able to do after school drop offs, pick ups, transportation to activities, and more. If you are looking for care over holiday break, I'm happy to provide that as well. 

Multiple personal and professional references available.

Hello, I am Jakiya I have experience working with all aged children from newborn up until 12 I enjoy doing all types of actives with children. I have experience with nannying and working in classroom settings, daycare, camps etc.

description.originalText: Jakiya does a wonderful job with my child. I have no worries when my daughter is with her. She cares and nutures my child. She is the best!  my daughter loves her. Keep doing a great Job

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, my name is Mariah! Working with children is my passion, and I have over 10 years of experience in childcare. For the past 7 years, I have also worked as a teacher, engaging with children from 3 months to high school age, including those with special needs.

I find immense joy in witnessing the growth and development of children, and I strive to create a positive and nurturing environment where they can thrive. It's incredibly rewarding to know that I can make a difference in their lives and bring a smile to their faces every day.

I would love the opportunity to discuss how I can contribute to your family!

description.originalText: Mariah is a very experienced, knowledgeable caregiver. She exhibits patience, compassion, and nurturing spirit to the youth!

bio.experienceSummary:
I moved to the US when I was 10 from France. I speak French fluently. 
I was around my siblings, one who is 10 years younger than me my whole childhood and helped take care of her. I am a painter and artist that worked in textile design until recently. I love to teach art of all kinds and be creative. I practice mindfulness, meditation and yoga. 
I'll love to talk about 'nerdy' things, especially science and space!

Hi all! I'm a Georgia Tech grad working full time as an engineer and part time as a babysitter for years now. I'm located in Grant Park and have families in Brookhaven, Druid Hills, Summerhill, Midtown and in between :) I have experience with newborns through preteens - references available if wanted. I am comfortable with pets and have my own transportation. In my free time I Orangetheory and tutor high school chemistry. I'm vaccinated and boosted. Please feel free to reach out with any questions!

description.originalText: Amy is a phenomenal sitter. She is kind, smart, and my child enjoyed his time with her. He usually isn’t thrilled about having a babysitter but her happiness and positive attitude is infectious and he can’t wait to see her again.

bio.experienceSummary: I am fun and outgoing and I love spending time with children. While I was in high school in Atlanta, Georgia, I gained over three years of experience working with children of various ages. After High School I spent two seasons coaching swim and diving my school. I can also help with light housekeeping and cooking/meal preparation. I am very active and I enjoy going on walks and the beach! I look forward to meeting your family and welcome the opportunity to help create happy memories for your children.

description.originalText: Lexie is the best, seriously we love her! She watched our LO from 1 month old till 6 months. She also sometimes watched our 3 year old too and was great with her. She always had fun things for the girls to do. She was great at calming our fussy nb and would go above and beyond to get her to nap. She is extremely caring and quickly became one of our family. You could tell how much she cared for our daughters. She was great a communicating, was always punctual, and flexible with our schedule. We miss having her around.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello,

I am a 23-year-old recent college graduate with a strong background in childcare. Known for being patient, reliable, and creative, I have a long history of caring for children of all ages for both family and friends. I aim to leverage this experience to assist parents needing dependable childcare.

I offer flexible availability and have my own transportation, ensuring I can accommodate various schedules and needs. With my skills and experience, I am committed to providing your children a supervised, safe, and nurturing environment.

I look forward to supporting your family and caring for your little ones.

As a nurturing and reliable childcare provider with over a decade of experience, I'm dedicated to fostering a safe and nurturing environment for your child. My passion for working with children stems from my desire to make a positive impact on their lives and support families in balancing their responsibilities.

My patient and calm demeanor, coupled with my creativity and imagination, allows me to connect with children of all ages. I believe in open communication with parents and provide regular updates on your child's day. I'm also experienced in enforcing household rules to ensure a consistent and structured environment.

From outdoor sports to educational games and technology-based activities, I'm always seeking new and engaging ways to entertain and teach children. My expertise includes caring for infants, toddlers, and school-aged children. With a background in early childhood education and training in First Aid and CPR, I'm well-equipped to handle any situation.

Hello! My name is Saunjere but most call me Sunny. I'm 22 years old and although I am young I have over 7 years of experience in working with kids! I started working at Bellevue Daycare Center when I was 14 years old. Since then I've worked at camps (JCC, Camp Saint Andrews, Camp Kelly, etc.) and other facilities as well! I also have been taking care of two of my younger siblings since the age of 13 years old. I have a car, I can travel to and from. I'm always smiling and very social! I enjoy working with kids very much! Thank you.

description.displayText: She was so great with my younger cousins. They enjoyed her very much. Will hire her again!
description.originalText: She was so great with my younger cousins. They enjoyed her very much. Will hire her again!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello there, my name is Chauntrice! With over 10 years of experience, I have had the privilege of caring for children of all ages. I have a genuine passion for assisting little ones in reaching their milestones, be it sleep training, schedules, feeding, basic sign language, tummy time, or potty training. Creating a safe, nurturing environment and prioritizing the well-being, growth, and development of children is at the core of what I do. I believe in the power of open and empathetic communication to forge strong connections with the children in my care. I am dedicated to making your life a bit easier by providing your children with the utmost compassion, patience, and understanding. I am genuinely looking forward to the opportunity to work with you and your family soon!

description.originalText:
I cannot say enough positive things about Chauntrice. She was absolutely amazing! From the moment she arrived, she was warm, friendly, and engaging with my daughter. She was incredibly responsible and attentive, making sure my daughter was safe and entertained at all times.

I was so impressed with her ability to handle any situation that arose with ease and confidence. She was patient, kind, and nurturing with my daughter, and it was clear that she genuinely cared about her well-being. I felt completely at ease leaving my daughter in her care and knew that she was in good hands.

I also appreciated the fact that she was punctual, organized, and communicated effectively with me throughout the evening. She went above and beyond my expectations and I would not hesitate to hire her again in the future. I highly recommend her to any parent looking for a reliable and trustworthy babysitter. Thank you for everything!
